<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="313" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1196,1943]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,563,1304,1332]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">
Description of 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[392,407,1304,1318]" fontSize="6" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">rd</superScript>
instar larva.
</emphasis>
Size (based on 
<specimenCount box="[747,905,1307,1332]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" type="generic">19 specimens</specimenCount>
): BL 
<quantity box="[970,1074,1307,1332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.72" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="9.72">9.72 mm</quantity>
; HL 
<quantity box="[1133,1234,1307,1332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.06" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="2.06">2.06 mm</quantity>
(1.87–2.22), HW 
<quantity box="[151,255,1342,1367]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.50 mm</quantity>
(2.25–2.70), ML 
<quantity box="[466,570,1342,1367]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.37" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="2.37">2.37 mm</quantity>
(2.19–2.58), HW/HL 1.21, ML/HL 1.15. General colouring greyish ochre thickly mottled with grey, dorsal side with a median paler stripe, ventral side paler, mottled with grey; dorsal side of the head capsule dark brown with conspicuous yellow markings (
<figureCitation box="[934,1033,1414,1439]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[230,1355,208,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-50@28.[213,1373,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Libelloides siculus (Angelini, 1827), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sicily, Madonie). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–e: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915229/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Fig. 16b</figureCitation>
), ventral side dark brown with two pale longitudinal markings (
<figureCitation box="[471,569,1451,1476]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[230,1355,208,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-50@28.[213,1373,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Libelloides siculus (Angelini, 1827), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sicily, Madonie). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–e: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915229/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Fig. 16d</figureCitation>
), mandibles dark brown; legs with dark brown coxae and yellowish femora, tibiae and tarsi (
<figureCitation box="[337,435,1486,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[230,1355,208,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-50@28.[213,1373,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Libelloides siculus (Angelini, 1827), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sicily, Madonie). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–e: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915229/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Fig. 16e</figureCitation>
); setae of the body black. Head wider than long, slightly dilated posteriorly; mandibles slightly longer than the head capsule (
<figureCitation box="[593,692,1523,1548]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[230,1355,208,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-50@28.[213,1373,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Libelloides siculus (Angelini, 1827), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sicily, Madonie). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–e: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915229/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Fig. 16a</figureCitation>
); interdental pseudo-teeth: (~4)(~2)(0–1); external margin of the mandible with short setae. Thorax and its scolus-like processes yellowish, visually distinct from the greyish abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[268,364,1595,1620]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[230,1355,208,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-50@28.[213,1373,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Libelloides siculus (Angelini, 1827), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sicily, Madonie). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–e: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915229/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Fig. 16c</figureCitation>
); pronotum dark brown with yellow stripes and covered with short setae; mesothoracic spiracles yellow with black apex. Abdominal spiracles dark brown; VIII sternite with brown spots covering the short odontoid processes; IX sternite yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[630,719,1667,1692]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[260,1345,203,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-58@2.[232,1354,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Taxonomic characters of Ascalaphidae larvae. A, Deleproctophylla australis dorsal and ventral view; B, head of Ascalaphus festivus; C, head of Puer maculatus; D, VIII and IX sternites of Libelloides siculus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915175/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1196,1943]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,1702,1727]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">Bio-ecology.</emphasis>
This species inhabits open, grassy habitats from the sea-level to the mountains (Madonie, Peloritani, Etna). The larvae are soil dwelling ambush hunters, as the other members of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,973,1774,1799]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1196,1943]" box="[199,973,1774,1799]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1774,1799]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Angelini" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[359,466,1774,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siculus">
