</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="313" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1196,1943]" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1811,1836]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Angelini" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[469,577,1811,1836]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siculus">
<emphasis box="[469,577,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">L. siculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognizable for the pale longitudinal markings on the ventral side of the head and the yellowish colour of the head markings, thorax and legs. The above mentioned characters also clearly differentiate 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Angelini" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[297,408,1883,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siculus">
<emphasis box="[297,408,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">L. siculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the closely related but allopatric 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Charpentier" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[865,995,1884,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ictericus">
<emphasis box="[865,995,1884,1907]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">L. ictericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1055,1181,1884,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corsicus">
<emphasis box="[1055,1181,1884,1907]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">L. corsicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Notably, this species shares its range with only one congener, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis et Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[607,734,1920,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coccajus">
<emphasis box="[607,734,1920,1943]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="313">L. coccajus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
